# <%= current_page.data.title %>

When the Circle CI service account token gets rotated, the Cloud Platform team will provide comms.

### 1. Check and Update the pipeline_variable script

fb-deploy repository (read the the [README](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/fb-deploy)) 

You'll need to update the `bin/pipeline_variables` bash script with the new token name.

There several different namespaces to get this infomation. The first one is from the formbuilder-deploy namespace.
Run `kubectl get secrets -n formbuilder-deploy`

Working through the script do the same for the other namespaces, formbuilder-platform, formbuilder-services etc.

Run the script with for the service needed to get the new token values. For example, for fb-editor run:

`./bin/pipeline_variables fb-editor`

### 2. Update the CircleCI context with the new token

In CircleCI > Org > Context > moj_forms - replace:

`EKS_CLUSTER_CERT`<br>
`EKS_TOKEN`

Keep the base64 encoding.  

> The last unmasked characters may be the same. Just replace them. 

### 3. Update individual pipelines with the new tokens

Run the script with for the service needed to get the new token values. For example, for fb-submitter run:

`./bin/pipeline_variables fb-submitter`

The context tokens (above) will be provided, further down will be the individual tokens for each namespace.

Go to the pipeline in CircleCI > Projects > ministryofjustice > fb-submitter > Project Settings > Environment Variables.

Update the following variables with the new tokens for each of the environment namespaces:

For platform and services namespaces:<br>
`EKS_TOKEN_LIVE_DEV`<br>
`EKS_TOKEN_TEST_PRODUCTION`<br>
`EKS_TOKEN_LIVE_DEV`<br>
`EKS_TOKEN_LIVE_PRODUCTION`

otherwise:<br>
`EKS_TOKEN_LIVE`<br>
`EKS_TOKEN_TEST`<br>
`EKS_TOKEN_STAGING`

Again, keep the base64 encoding.
